        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 2:12PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 211 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Athens, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Athens, Fayetteville, Meridianville, Hazel Green, Ardmore, Harvest,
Lincoln, French Mill, Elkwood, and Belleview.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
